The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Corporate Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Corporate Briefs
                              
	 Infosys Technologies has signed an agreement to implement Finacle universal banking solution at financial services group BBVA. BBVA plans to invest 5.6 billion euros in the technology over the next three years and its innovation and transformational plan launched in 2007 aims to improve cost efficiencies and productivity. The bank will start the transformation exercise in BBVA Banco (Paraguay) and will implement Finacle core banking, customer relationship management, treasury and wealth management solutions.                            
	 The net turnover of Gujarat Narmada Valley Fertilizers (GNVF) for the financial year ended March 31, 2008 has grown 25 per cent to Rs 3,433.91 crore from Rs 2,739.27 crore in the previous fiscal. Profit before tax grew 18 per cent in the reporting period to Rs 576.21 crore from Rs 489.39 crore while profit after tax grew 14 per cent to Rs 372.88 crore from Rs 326.47 crore. The board has kept the dividend unaltered at Rs 4.25 per share.                            
	 Indian Railways Catering and Tourism Corporation Ltd (IRCTC) has recognised ngpay as one of the leading mobile sales channel for rail tickets in India. ngpay enables customers transact with merchants, banks, and service providers through mobile handsets. IRCTCs deployment on ngpay allows customers to check fares, routes and book tickets from their mobiles.                            
	 Merlin Group has launched Singapore City, the internationally designed integrated development project at Raipur in central India. The project, spread over 25 acres and valued at Rs 300 crore, will be jointly developed by the Merlin group and Singhania Buildcon group.                             
	 Air Deccan has announced its summer special bonanza for online bookings through its website. There are exclusive 2-nights/3-day holiday package to be won in the offer period. The airline itself will pay for the package. The offer is valid between July 1, 2008 and September 30, 2008.                             
	 Firstsource Solutions and Bharti Airtel have signed a three-year outsourcing agreement. Firstsource will provide a suite of BPO services to Airtel from its centres in Chennai and Mumbai. It expects to have over 1,000 employees in the first year to provide services in English and eight other regional languages to Airtel customers.                            
	 Chittaranjan Locomotive Works (CLW) has launched its renovated website, which is designed according to the guidelines issued by the Railway Board and the central vigilance commission.                                                                               
	 Zodiac has launched the linen collection for summer 2008 called Positano. The collection comprising striped designs in linen are available across all retail and multi-brand stores and is priced at Rs 1,699.                                                                                                                  ADVERTISEMENT                   
